Tashkent Institute of Water Supply, Sewerage, Hydrotechnical Structures and Engineering Hydrogeology (ToshNII 'VODGEO'), was established in 1960 as a laboratory of water management of the settlement industry at the Central Asian Research Institute of Architecture and Construction, in 1964 it became 'VODGEO' The department of water management at the All-Union Scientific Research Institute, and in 1978 'VODGEO' was transformed into the Tashkent branch of the All-Union Scientific Research Institute. Since December 1992, the institute has been a constituent unit of the State Committee for Nature Protection of the Republic of Uzbekistan. In order to fulfill the decree of the President of the Republic of Uzbekistan dated April 21, 2017 No. PQ-2915 'On measures to ensure the organization of the activities of the State Committee for Ecology and Environmental Protection of the Republic of Uzbekistan', as well as in accordance with orders No. 146 and No. 17, No. 91 dated April 26, 2017. According to the information of the certificate No. 538681 of August 21, 2017, the State Committee for Ecology and Environmental Protection of the Republic of Uzbekistan, the Research Institute of Ecology and Environmental Protection of the Republic of Uzbekistan started its work. Scientific Research Institute of Ecology and Environmental Protection under the State Ecology Committee of the Republic of Uzbekistan was the legal successor of ToshITI 'SUVGEO', 'ITLTI ATMOSFERA' and NPGP 'Ecology of Water Management'. Implementation of the decision of the Cabinet of Ministers of the Republic of Uzbekistan dated November 26, 2018 No. 958 'On measures to further develop the scientific research base in the field of ecology and environmental protection', as well as the Republic of Uzbekistan on Ecology According to the order of the state committee No. 417 dated November 29, 2018 and environmental protection 'Research Institute of Ecology and Environmental Protection under the State Ecology Committee of the Republic of Uzbekistan' State of the Republic of Uzbekistan It was transformed into the Scientific-Research Institute of Environment and Nature Protection Technologies under the Ecology Committee. The institute is engaged in the development of normative and methodological documents in the field of processing and disposal of industrial and household waste, environmental protection. The activity of the Institute is aimed at solving the current and prospective tasks of the State Committee for Nature Protection in the field of natural resources protection. At present, developments in cleaning waste and natural waters from toxic substances, heavy metals, biogenic elements, cleaning water, soil and soil from oil products are of the greatest interest and relevance. The institute is aimed at reducing pollution in our republic and reducing the amount of waste water discharged from industrial, agricultural and communal facilities into natural water sources. solves problems. The city develops measures for the treatment and post-treatment of domestic and industrial waste water, their mixtures, to achieve standards for discharge into the sewage system and open water bodies, thereby reducing the anthropogenic pressure on open water bodies and the environment. Water Resources Protection Laboratory The laboratory provides services in the development of treatment and post-treatment technology for domestic and industrial waste water and their mixtures, which allows to achieve discharge rates to the municipal sewage system and open water bodies, thereby reducing the impact on open water bodies and the environment. reduces anthropogenic pressure. Biotesting services. Develops regulatory documents such as ZVOS, ZEP, PDV, PDO, PDS, RSV.
 The 'Development of waste processing and disposal technologies' department unites the scientific developments of the Republic, scientists and specialists from the structural division of the institute. among other things, it carries out its scientific and technological developments and works on the use of secondary raw materials in the sectors of the republic's economy. Atmospheric air protection laboratory. The main directions of the laboratory's activity: 
 - solving the tasks of carrying out research on the development and design of methods and equipment that reduce air pollution from the emissions of harmful substances from industrial enterprises; 
 - toxic industry that pollutes the atmosphere, rural areas economy, disposal, processing and destruction of household waste;
– measures to develop the inventory and reduce the emission of pollutants into the atmosphere, calculation of the environmental risk category of enterprises.

 Department of Biodiversity Conservation The main problem is that biodiversity is not sustainable. It recognizes the interconnectedness and interconnectedness of all biological parts of nature. Often, there are three types of this concept:
– species biodiversity - the diversity of all plants and animals, including different bacteria and microorganisms;
– genetic diversity - the diversity of the genetic material of a species and biodiversity between them;
– different ecological systems - the richness of ecological systems (for example, mountain forests, deserts or savannas, deserts and seas, etc.).
 Together, these three types of biodiversity constitutes diversity. Therefore, maintaining each of these levels is critical to maintaining biodiversity as a whole. The main tasks of the laboratory for the protection of land resources are aimed at improving the ecological and amelioration situation and protecting the soil environment in the territory of the Republic of Uzbekistan. Decrees of the President of the Republic of Uzbekistan:
– 'On the strategy of actions for the further development of the Republic of Uzbekistan', No. UP-4947 of February 7, 2017;
– 'Protection of lands, their rational use', on measures to improve the activities of geodesy and cartography, and to strengthen control over the regulation of state cadastre administration' dated May 31, 2017 No. UP-5065; Decision on measures to further improve the forest management system;
 Other normative documents related to this activity serve to some extent the results of scientific research of this laboratory. During its activity, the Institute completed more than 2,000 scientific research works, most of which were used in the design and construction of national economy objects in the Republic of Uzbekistan, the Union Republics, the current CIS countries, as well as abroad (Germany, Estonia). The Institute participated in the development of the Law of the Republic of Uzbekistan 'On Waste', adopted at the 8th session of the Oliy Majlis in 2002, and 25 regulatory and methodological documents were developed. The institute's works presented at international forums, exhibitions and competitions were awarded as follows:
– silver medals, 1st and 2nd degree diplomas were received at the VDNX exhibitions of the USSR and Uz SSR;
– one at the International Exhibition of New Technologies and Product Inventions received silver and two bronze medals (Geneva, Switzerland);
 – received two gold medals at the 1st International Congress on Health and Environment (Manila, Philippines);
